7.31	Nykesha_Sales	Nykesha Sales	Nykesha Simone Sales (born May 10, 1976 in Bloomfield, Connecticut) is a former professional basketball player in the WNBA, most recently for the Connecticut Sun. Her primary position is the small forward. Her second position is shooting guard. In 1999 Sales was added to the roster of the USA FIBA Senior National Team team. Her brother Brooks Sales played forward for Villanova from 1998–2002, and currently plays overseas in Spain for the Club Baloncesto Breogán of Lugo.	
